The Chinese mainland recorded 112 confirmed COVID-19 cases on Monday, with 69 attributed to local transmissions and 43 from overseas, data from the National Health Commission showed on Tuesday. A total of 306 asymptomatic cases were also recorded on Monday, and 1,774 asymptomatic patients remain under medical observation. The cumulative number of confirmed cases on the Chinese mainland is 226,035, with the death toll from COVID-19 standing at 5,226. The latest tally of confirmed cases in the Hong Kong and Macao special administrative regions and Taiwan region is as follows: Hong Kong: 339,164 (64,265 recoveries, 9,405 deaths) Macao: 400 (83 recoveries, two deaths) Taiwan: 3,893,643 (13,742 recoveries, 7,025 deaths)